Sample metadata table

sample_metadata_sub2k.Rd

This is a meta-data/mapping file containing related information about samples originated from the Earth Microbiome Project.

sample_metadata_sub2k

Format

Data frame with columns

#SampleID

unique sample identifier (leading hashtag is required by Qiime)

BarcodeSequence

barcode sequence

LinkerPrimerSequence

linker primer sequence

Description

sample description

host_subject_id

unique host or subject (can have multiple samples per host_subject_id)

study_id

study identifier

title

study title

principal_investigator

PI of the study

doi

Digital Object Identifier (DOI) or PubMed ID of primary publication

ebi_accession

European Bioinformatics Institute (EBI) European Nucleotide Archive (ENA) accession number if submitted

target_gene

name of gene amplified (e.g., 16S rRNA)

target_subfragment

name of subfragment of gene amplified (e.g., V4)

pcr_primers

amplicon primer sequences used

illumina_technology

model of Illumina sequencer

extraction_center

where the sample was physically extracted

run_center

where the sample was physically sequenced (CCME=U Colorado Boulder, ANL=Argonne Natl Lab, UCSDMI=UC San Diego, CGS-GL=Wash U, UCD=U Colorado Denver)

run_date

date the sample was physically sequenced

read_length_bp

median read length in bp across study after quality filtering

sequences_split_libraries

number of sequences after demultiplexing with split_libraries_fastq.py

observations_closed_ref_greengenes

number of observations in closed-reference Greengenes table

observations_closed_ref_silva

number of observations in closed-reference Silva table

observations_open_ref_greengenes

number of observations in open-reference Greengenes table

observations_deblur_90bp

number of observations in 90-bp Deblur table

observations_deblur_100bp

number of observations in 100-bp Deblur table

observations_deblur_150bp

number of observations in 150-bp Deblur table

emp_release1

samples with >=1 sequences (split libraries) per sample

qc_filtered

samples with >=1000 observations in CR-GG & CR-Silva & OR-GG & Deblur-90 but excluding controls (all subsets are in this set)

subset_10k

10000 samples with >=10000 CR-GG & CR-Silva & OR-GG and >=5000 Deblur-90, randomly selected and evenly distributed across empo_3 categories and then across studies

subset_5k

5000 samples with >=10000 CR-GG & CR-Silva & OR-GG and >=5000 Deblur-90, randomly selected and evenly distributed across empo_3 categories and then across studies

subset_2k

2000 samples with >=10000 CR-GG & CR-Silva & OR-GG and >=5000 Deblur-90, randomly selected and evenly distributed across empo_3 categories and then across studies

sample_taxid

sample NCBI taxonomy ID

sample_scientific_name

sample NCBI scientific name looked up from taxonomy ID

host_taxid

host NCBI taxonomy ID

host_common_name_provided

host common name provided in the original mapping file

host_common_name

host NCBI common name looked up from taxonomy ID

host_scientific_name

host NCBI scientific name looked up from taxonomy ID

host_superkingdom

host superkingdom looked up from taxonomy ID

host_kingdom

host kingdom looked up from taxonomy ID

host_phylum

host phylum looked up from taxonomy ID

host_class

host class looked up from taxonomy ID

host_order

host order looked up from taxonomy ID

host_family

host family looked up from taxonomy ID

host_genus

host genus looked up from taxonomy ID

host_species

host species looked up from taxonomy ID

collection_timestamp

date and time when sample was collected

country

country where sample was collected

latitude_deg

latitude in degrees

longitude_deg

longitude in degrees

depth_m

depth in meters of sample below surface (earth surface if soil, sea/lake bottom if sediment, lake surface if lake, sea level if marine)

altitude_m

height above surface, usually zero unless the mouse is levitating (either depth or altitude can have a non-zero value but not both)

elevation_m

height above sea level in meters (from georeferencing tool)

env_biome

ENVO biome

env_feature

ENVO feature

env_material

ENVO material

envo_biome_0

level 0 ENVO biome looked up from given ENVO biome

envo_biome_1

level 1 ENVO biome looked up from given ENVO biome

envo_biome_2

level 2 ENVO biome looked up from given ENVO biome

envo_biome_3

level 3 ENVO biome looked up from given ENVO biome

envo_biome_4

level 4 ENVO biome looked up from given ENVO biome

envo_biome_5

level 5 ENVO biome looked up from given ENVO biome

empo_0

level 0 EMPO habitat from EMPO ontology

empo_1

level 1 EMPO habitat from EMPO ontology

empo_2

level 2 EMPO habitat from EMPO ontology

empo_3

level 3 EMPO habitat from EMPO ontology

adiv_observed_otus

observed tag sequences of 90-bp Deblur table rarefied to 5000 sequences per sample

adiv_chao1

Chao1 index of 90-bp Deblur table rarefied to 5000 sequences per sample

adiv_shannon

Shannon index of 90-bp Deblur table rarefied to 5000 sequences per sample

adiv_faith_pd

Faith's phylogenetic diversity of 90-bp Deblur table rarefied to 5000 sequences per sample

temperature_deg_c

ambient temperature in degrees Celcius

ph

pH value

salinity_psu

salinity in practical salinity units (PSU)

oxygen_mg_per_l

oxygen concentration in mg/L

phosphate_umol_per_l

phosphate concentration in µmol/L

ammonium_umol_per_l

ammonium concentration in µmol/L

nitrate_umol_per_l

nitrate concentration in µmol/L

sulfate_umol_per_l

sulfate concentration in µmol/L

Source

https://earthmicrobiome.org/
